<paragraph blockId="15.[189,342,780,806]" box="[189,342,780,806]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,342,780,806]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,342,780,806]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Distribution</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="15.[189,1399,827,958]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
This taxon has a more northerly distribution than the other species of 
<taxonomicName box="[1040,1213,827,853]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plantaginaceae" genus="Ameroglossum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1040,1213,827,853]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Ameroglossum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and occurs the lowest for this genus. It occurs on rock outcrops in the Agreste Paraibano mesoregion, in 
<collectingRegion country="Brazil" name="Paraiba" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Paraíba State</collectingRegion>
(two populations), and in the Agreste Potiguar mesoregion in 
<collectingRegion box="[1006,1330,896,923]" country="Brazil" name="Rio Grande do Norte" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Rio Grande do Norte State</collectingRegion>
(four populations), 
<collectingCountry box="[350,425,931,957]" name="Brazil" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Brazil</collectingCountry>
. Elevation between 70 and 
<specimenCount box="[748,830,931,957]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" type="generic">
<quantity box="[748,825,931,957]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" unit="m" value="300.0">300 m</quantity>
.
</specimenCount>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
